wikipedia_page.main: Thomas Alexander Nagle was an Irish Labour Party politician. He was elected to Dáil Éireann as a Labour Party Teachta Dála (TD) for the Cork Mid, North, South, South East and West constituency at the 1922 general election. He was re-elected at the 1923 general election for the Cork North constituency. He lost his seat at the June 1927 general election.
